</i> ‘strength’. The name is not found in England immediately after the Conquest, but only in the later Middle English period. It may have been introduced by migrants from the Low Countries who came to England in connection with the cloth trade, and was certainly in consistent use in some areas throughout the 16th and 17th centuries, although it was not generally popular until the 19th century, when many medieval names were revived. It has now fallen from favour again."],"variants":[]}],"lifeSummary":"When Gertrude de Marieux was born in 1084, in Marieux, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France, her father, Oscar de Marieux, was 32 and her mother, Jehanne de Beauquesne, was 23. She married Auguste de Warluzel about 1104, in Marieux, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France. They were the parents of at least 1 son. She died in 1137, in Warluzel, Pas-de-Calais, Hauts-de-France, France, at the age of 53."},"et":{"1084–1137":"1084–1137","1080–1129":"1080–1129","1081–1135":"1081–1135","1082–1127":"1082–1127","1092–1143":"1092–1143","1078–1136":"1078–1136","1112–1169":"1112–1169","1052–1103":"1052–1103","1061–1109":"1061–1109","1080":"1080","1143":"1143","Abt 1104":"umbes 1104","1052":"1052","1084":"1084","1061":"1061","1082":"1082","1092":"1092","1081":"1081","1129":"1129","1127":"1127","1137":"1137","1103":"1103","1136":"1136","1169":"1169","1135":"1135","1112":"1112","1079":"1079","1078":"1078","1109":"1109","Marieux, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France":"Marieux, Somme, Hauts-de-France, Prantsusmaa","Beauquesne, Somme, Hauts-de-France, France":"Beauquesne, Somme, Hauts-de-France, Prantsusmaa","Warluzel, Pas-de-Calais, Hauts-de-France, France":"Warluzel, Pas-de-Calais, Hauts-de-France, Prantsusmaa"},"fi":{"1084–1137":"1084–1137","1080–1129":"1080–1129","1081–1135":"1081–1135","1082–1127":"1082–1127","1092–1143":"1092–1143","1078–1136":"1078–1136","1112–1169":"1112–1169","1052–1103":"1052–1103","1061–1109":"1061–1109","1080":"1080","1143":"1143","Abt 1104":"noin 1104","1052":"1052","1084":"108